            "title": "World Hemophilia Day 2026 - April 17, 2026 - \"Diagnosis: First step to care.\"",
            "id": "4120d644-5c0b-46fa-b2cb-41e99bdb5ef5",
            "description": "Today, April 17, 2026, marks World Hemophilia Day, when the worldwide community affected by inherited bleeding disorders unites to raise awareness. The theme for this year, \"Diagnosis: First step to care,\" underscores the crucial role of early identification in managing these disorders. This annual event serves as a platform for advocacy, with the global community emphasizing the need for improved care and support for those with inherited bleeding disorders.",
